<h3>How to use:</h3>
<p>First, apply base styling to prep element for animation.</p>
{{ '```scss
.class {
  @include bolt-animation--zoom-in($base: true);
}
```' | markdown }}
<p>Next, apply the same mixin with <code>$base: true</code> to the css.</p>
<p>For example, to trigger the animation on hover...</p>
{{ '```scss
.class {
  @include bolt-animation--zoom-in($base: true);
  &:hover {
    @include bolt-animation--zoom-in($active: true);
  }
}
```' | markdown }}
<p>Additionally, animations can be tied to data attributes that are applied with the javascript animation utitilites provided through <code>@bolt/animations</code>.</p>
{{ '```scss
.class {
  @include bolt-animation--zoom-in($base: true);
  &[data-anim-triggered="yes"] {
    @include bolt-animation--zoom-in($active: true);
  }
}
```' | markdown }}
<p>Or the animation can be fired without a triggering event.</p>
{{ '```scss
.class {
  @include bolt-animation--zoom-in($base: true, $active: true);
}
```' | markdown }}

<h2>Customizing Animations</h2>
<p>Animation mixins are fully customizable. For example, here are a number of 'heart beat' animations with various Bolt animation settings applied.</p>

